<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CONNECTING
        ROD, PISTON &#38; RING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CONNECTING ROD, PISTON &#38; RING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using pliers, remove the two piston retaining rings. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050608">6.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050607" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2410" filename="../figeg2/eg2410.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.7.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Forcing Nut</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Sleeve Puller</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Lifting Bridge</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Cylinder Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Lifting Bridge and Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Lifting Jaws</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050608" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2411" filename="../figeg2/eg2411.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.8.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the piston pin from its bore, by hand. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_109.xml" xrefid="ef1050609">6.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Then separate the connecting rod from the piston.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a piston ring expander tool to remove the piston rings. remove the top ring first,
                    then the intermediate ring and the oil control ring. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_109.xml" xrefid="ef1050610">6.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tag or mark the components with the cylinder number from which they were removed, so
                    they may be reinstalled in their respective cylinders once inspected.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
